# Example environment variables for md-semantic-search (mdss)
# https://github.com/chelslava/md-semantic-search
#
# Copy into your shell profile / .env and substitute ABSOLUTE paths to YOUR copy
# of this knowledge base. With these set you can call `mdss index` / `mdss search`
# without --db/--index-dir.
# (The kb-index.* / kb-search.* wrappers resolve paths themselves — env vars are
#  only needed for direct `mdss` calls.)

# Knowledge base root (this repo's folder).
# Windows example:  MDSS_DB=C:/Users/you/agent-knowledge-base
# POSIX example:    MDSS_DB=/home/you/agent-knowledge-base
MDSS_DB=/path/to/agent-knowledge-base

# Where to store the index (default <db>/.mdss; here we keep it under semantic/.mdss)
MDSS_INDEX_DIR=/path/to/agent-knowledge-base/semantic/.mdss

# Embedding-model cache (default <package>/.cache)
# MDSS_CACHE_DIR=/path/to/agent-knowledge-base/semantic/.cache

# Model used by the kb-index.* wrappers (default bge-m3). Uncomment to override:
# MDSS_MODEL=e5-base

# Notes (verified against the tool's source):
# - This base's model: bge-m3 = Xenova/bge-m3 (1024d, ~2.3 GB) — maximum
#   cross-lingual separation. The tool's own default is e5-base (768d, ~280 MB).
#   A direct `mdss` call uses e5-base unless you pass --model bge-m3.
#   Changing the model -> full reindex (incompatible dimensions).
# - dot-folders (.mdss/.cache/.git) are skipped by the indexer automatically.
# - Service folders are excluded with flags: --ignore "semantic/**" --ignore "templates/**".
# - There is no hard relevance threshold: the anti-duplicate decision is made from
#   the top results (cosine ~0.80+ usually means a strong match; see knowledge-rules.md).
